node.title: Victoria records 1,206 new COVID-19 cases and two deaths
node.alt: Pedestrians walk across a crossing on a Moonee Ponds street, with Christmas decorations hanging from shops.
node.description: There are now 11,145 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 582 people have died during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,206\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and two\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 11,145\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 582\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 313\u00a0people in hospital, of whom 61\u00a0are in intensive care and 25\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "A further 43\u00a0people are in ICU but their infections are no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 66,784\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,925\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
